2 STUDY THE PROVISION OF MEDICAL AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CARE IN
3 JAILS
4 SECTION 9.(a) The North Carolina Collaboratory (Collaboratory) shall study the
5 provision of medical and behavioral health care delivered in county jails in the State and make
6 recommendations to improve the health care provided to individuals in custody. The
7 Collaboratory shall consult with relevant stakeholders, including local partners, the Sheriffs'
8 Association, and the Department of Health and Human Services. The study shall include at least
9 all of the following:
10 (1) A review of intake screening procedures used in county jails for identifying
11 medical and behavioral health conditions.
12 (2) An examination of current health care provider arrangements, including
13 in-house services, contracted services, hybrid models, or other recommended
14 approaches for delivering care in county jails.
15 (3) An assessment of policies and practices for responding to behavioral health
16 crises within jail settings.
17 (4) An evaluation of existing staffing models for medical and behavioral health
18 services in county jails.
19 (5) The development of recommendations for potential expansion of the North
20 Carolina Safekeeper Program.
21 (6) Any other information deemed relevant by the Collaboratory to improve the
22 provision of medical and behavioral health care in jails.
23 SECTION 9.(b) No later than December 1, 2026, the Collaboratory shall submit a
24 progress report on the study as required in subsection (a) of this section to the Joint Legislative
25 Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services. No later than March 1, 2027, the
26 Collaboratory shall submit a final report on the study as required in subsection (a) of this section
27 to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services.
28
29 THE NORTH CAROLINA COLLABORATORY TO STUDY FEASIBILITY OF THE
30 CHANGE OF OPERATION OR ADMINISTRATION OF STATE-OPERATED
31 PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITALS
32 SECTION 10.(a) The North Carolina Collaboratory (Collaboratory) is directed to
33 explore the feasibility of improving the provision of services at Broughton Hospital, Central
34 Regional Hospital, and Cherry Hospital (collectively, the Hospitals). The Collaboratory is
35 directed to study and offer recommendations about the following:
36 (1) The feasibility of transferring full operation of the Hospitals from DHHS to
37 another entity.
38 (2) The feasibility of transferring certain operations of the Hospitals from DHHS
39 to another entity.
40 (3) Any services that another entity could provide to DHHS to assist DHHS in the
41 provision of services at the Hospitals.
42 (4) Any other operational or administrative initiatives relating to the provision of
43 services at the Hospitals.
44 (5) Reviewing and updating any previous studies or recommendations that may
45 be relevant or informative.
46 (6) Any financial impact (savings or additional costs), any impact on patient
47 outcomes, and any improvement in staffing to result from the implementation
48 of the recommendations provided according to this section.
49 SECTION 10.(b) The Department of Health and Human Services shall cooperate
50 fully with the Collaboratory in providing any data or assistance necessary for the Collaboratory
51 to complete the research required by subsection (a) of this section.
