36 "§ 122C-265. Outpatient commitment; examination and treatment pending hearing.
37 (a) If a respondent, who has been recommended for outpatient commitment by [a]
38 commitment examiner different from the proposed outpatient treatment physician or center, fails
39 to appear for examination by the proposed outpatient treatment physician or center at the
40 designated time, the physician or center shall notify the clerk of superior court who shall issue
41 an order to a law enforcement officer to take the respondent into custody and take him
42 immediately to the outpatient treatment physician or center for evaluation. The custody order is
43 valid throughout the State. The law-enforcement officer may wait during the examination and
44 return the respondent to his home after the examination.
45 (b) The examining commitment examiner or the proposed outpatient treatment physician
46 or center provider may prescribe to the respondent reasonable and appropriate medication and
47 treatment that are consistent with accepted medical standards pending the district court hearing.
48 (c) In no event may a respondent released on a recommendation that he or she meets the
49 outpatient commitment criteria be physically forced to take medication or forcibly detained for
50 treatment pending a district court hearing.
