1 procedures, orders, and conditions provided in Article 26 of this Chapter, Bail, specifically
2 including the power to place the defendant in the custody of a designated person or organization
3 agreeing to supervise him.
4 (c) If the defendant is placed in the custody of a hospital or other institution in a
5 proceeding for involuntary civil commitment, the orders must provide for reporting to the clerk
6 if the defendant is to be released from the custody of the hospital or institution. The original or
7 supplemental orders may make provisions as in subsection (b) in the event that the defendant is
8 released. The court shall also order that the defendant shall be examined to determine whether
9 the defendant has the capacity to proceed prior to release from custody. A report of the
