28 SECTION 13.(f) G.S. 15A-1006 reads as rewritten:
29 "§ 15A-1006. Return of defendant for trial upon gaining capacity.
30 If a defendant who has been determined to be incapable of proceeding, and who is in the
31 custody of an institution or an individual, has been determined by the institution or individual
32 having custody to have gained capacity to proceed, the individual or institution shall provide
33 written notification to the clerk in the county in which the criminal proceeding is pending. The
34 clerk shall provide written notification to the district attorney, the defendant's attorney, and the
35 sheriff. The sheriff shall return the defendant to the county for a supplemental hearing pursuant
36 to G.S. 15A-1007, if conducted, and trial and hold the defendant for a supplemental hearing and
37 trial, subject to the orders of the court entered pursuant to G.S. 15A-1004.
38 "§ 15A-1006. Return of defendant for supplemental hearing and trial upon gaining
39 capacity; discharge and return of defendant from involuntary commitment.
40 (a) When the clerk is notified that a defendant has likely gained capacity to proceed to
41 trial, the clerk shall provide written notification to the district attorney and the defendant's
42 attorney within 72 hours, and the matter shall proceed to a supplemental hearing pursuant to
43 G.S. 15A-1007, if conducted, and trial upon the court's determination that the defendant has
44 gained capacity to proceed. If the defendant is currently enrolled in any court-ordered capacity
45 restoration program pursuant to G.S. 15A-1003(a), this requirement shall remain in effect
46 pending the supplemental hearing.
47 (b) When a defendant who is charged with a violent crime, including a crime involving
48 assault with a deadly weapon, has likely gained capacity to proceed while involuntarily
49 committed, the clerk shall provide further written notification to the sheriff, who shall return the
50 defendant to the county for a supplemental hearing pursuant to G.S. 15A-1007, if conducted, and
51 trial and hold the defendant for a supplemental hearing and trial, subject to orders of the court
