1 entered pursuant to G.S. 15A-1003. Any defendant held in custody under this subsection may be
2 required to participate in capacity restoration services pending the supplemental hearing, if
3 reasonably available."
4 SECTION 13.(g) G.S. 15A-1007 reads as rewritten:
5 "§ 15A-1007. Supplemental capacity hearings.
6 (a) When it has been reported to the court that a defendant has gained capacity to proceed,
7 or when the defendant has been determined by the individual or institution having custody of him
8 to have gained capacity and has been returned for trial, in accordance with G.S. 15A-1004(e) and
9 G.S. 15A-1006, the clerk shall notify the district attorney. Upon receiving the notification, the
10 district attorney shall calendar the matter for hearing at the next available term of court but no
11 later than 30 days after receiving the notification. The court may hold a supplemental hearing to
12 determine whether the defendant has capacity to proceed. The court may take any action at the
13 supplemental hearing that it could have taken at an original hearing to determine the capacity of
14 the defendant to proceed.
15 (b) The court may hold a supplemental hearing any time upon its own determination that
16 a hearing is appropriate or necessary to inquire into the condition of the defendant.
17 (c) The court must hold a supplemental hearing if it appears that any of the conditions
18 for dismissal of the charges have been met.
19 (d) If the court determines in a supplemental hearing that a defendant has gained the
20 capacity to proceed, the case shall be calendared for trial at the earliest practicable time.
21 Continuances that extend beyond 60 days after initial calendaring of the trial shall be granted
22 only in extraordinary circumstances when necessary for the proper administration of justice, and
23 the court shall issue a written order stating the grounds for granting the continuance.
24 (a) Upon receiving notification from the clerk under G.S. 15A-1006 that a defendant has
25 likely gained capacity to proceed, the district attorney shall calendar the matter for hearing within
26 30 days of receiving the notification or at the next available term of court. The court may hold a
27 supplemental hearing to determine whether the defendant has capacity to proceed. The parties
28 may stipulate to the defendant's capacity but not to the defendant's lack of capacity. If the parties
29 stipulate to a finding of capacity, the judge may review new evidence, including new evaluations,
30 and make a determination of capacity without holding a hearing.
31 (b) If the court determines that a defendant has gained the capacity to proceed, the case
32 shall be calendared for trial at the earliest practicable time. Continuances that extend beyond 60
33 days after initial calendaring of the trial shall be granted only in extraordinary circumstances
34 when necessary for the proper administration of justice, and the court shall issue a written order
35 stating the grounds for granting the continuance. The court may order the defendant to receive
36 capacity restoration services pending further criminal proceedings if the court finds that such
37 services are reasonably available and reasonably necessary to ensure the defendant's capacity
38 does not deteriorate.
39 (c) The court shall hold a supplemental capacity hearing within a reasonable time after
40 any of the following:
41 (1) When the defendant has been ordered to participate in a capacity restoration
42 program pursuant to G.S. 15A-1003(a) and the program has not reported to
43 the clerk that the defendant has gained capacity to proceed prior to the end of
44 the defendant's enrollment period.
45 (2) Every four months if, pursuant to G.S. 15A-1003(b), the court has previously
46 waived the requirement for capacity restoration services.
47 (3) Every four months if, pursuant to G.S. 15A-1003(c), the defendant has been
48 found not likely to gain capacity within the foreseeable future and the charges
49 have not already been disposed.
50 (4) When it appears to the court that any of the conditions for disposition under
51 G.S. 15A-1008 have been met.
