32 SECTION 13.(h) G.S. 15A-1008 reads as rewritten:
33 "§ 15A-1008. Dismissal of charges.charges; referral of defendant for civil commitment
34 proceedings upon dismissal.
35 (a) When a defendant lacks capacity to proceed, the court shall dismiss the charges upon
36 the earliest of the following occurrences:
37 (1) When it appears to the satisfaction of the court that the defendant will not gain
38 capacity to proceed.
39 (2) When as a result of incarceration, involuntary commitment to an inpatient
40 facility, or other court-ordered confinement, the defendant has been
41 substantially deprived of his liberty for a period of time equal to or in excess
42 of the maximum term of imprisonment permissible for prior record Level VI
43 for felonies or prior conviction Level III for misdemeanors for the most
44 serious offense charged.
45 (3) Upon the expiration of a period of five years from the date of determination
46 of incapacity to proceed in the case of misdemeanor charges and a period of
47 10 years in the case of felony charges.
48 (b) A dismissal entered pursuant to subdivision (2) of subsection (a) of this section shall
49 be without leave.
50 (c) A dismissal entered pursuant to subdivision (1) or (3) of subsection (a) of this section
51 shall be issued without prejudice to the refiling of the charges.
